Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.11,0:42:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you were always a little bit off and now\Nhe's really off.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.68,0:42:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Why do they say that? Because\Nwe said these are two different
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.76,0:42:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigms of reality. The linear\NNewtonian paradigm, the one of supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.72,0:43:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,rational\Nworld of science and logic and the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.07,0:43:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect university\Nis one paradigm of reality. The
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.56,0:43:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear is not real. is not real to\Nthe Newtonian dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.72,0:43:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not real. So a person whose\Nawareness is confined to being a oneeyed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.80,0:43:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,man thinks that the vision of a two-eyed\Nman is bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.16,0:43:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right. So in the world of the blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.07,0:43:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the oneeyed man is king. But in the\Nworld of the oneeyed, the two-eyed man
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.04,0:43:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,again is strange.\NSo to the person limited to the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.44,0:43:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian paradigm of reality, they are\Nlike the oneeyed man.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.76,0:43:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you become spiritually aware,\Nit's like you have two eyes and now you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.16,0:43:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have you see things in three dimensions,\Nwhereas they only see them in two. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.72,0:43:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, yes, the family members, they can\Ncon consider you've gone off the deep
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.04,0:44:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,end and, um, quite insane. But, uh,\Nthat's all right because,
